<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="171" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="171">Distribution and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="171">This species is known only from southern Arizona, although its distribution likely extends into Mexico. The larva and its food plants are unknown. Adults were collected in July, August, and September.</paragraph>
